In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims September 22, 2015, as National Voter Registration Day. He highlights the importance of voting as a fundamental right that represents equality and civic participation. The President encourages all eligible Americans to register to vote and exercise this essential right. He emphasizes that the responsibility of perfecting the nation lies with its citizens, and the government can only do so much. He urges individuals to honor those who fought for the right to vote by actively participating in the political process. The President also acknowledges that the United States has one of the lowest voting rates among free societies and emphasizes the importance of electing strong leaders to build the kind of world we want for future generations. He calls upon all Americans to observe National Voter Registration Day by registering to vote.